cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code in your research or teaching, please cite it as below."
type: software

title: "carlin-soskice-open-economy"
abstract: >
  R implementation of the open-economy three-equation macroeconomic model
  (IS-PC-MR framework with UIP and RX curve) presented in Chapter 11 of
  Carlin & Soskice (2023). Includes period-by-period shock simulations
  (inflation, demand, supply, and world interest rate shocks) and
  ggplot2 visualizations of impulse response functions and model diagrams
  (PC-MR, IS-RX, AD-ERU). Developed as teaching material for advanced
  undergraduate economics courses.

authors:
  - family-names: "Dionisio Valverde Ambriz"
    given-names: "Ismael"
    affiliation: "Facultad de Economía, Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México"

repository-code: "https://github.com/ismaelvaleconomics/carlin-soskice-open-economy"
license: MIT
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-03-07"

keywords:
  - macroeconomics
  - open economy
  - three-equation model
  - monetary policy
  - exchange rate
  - uncovered interest parity
  - overshooting
  - Carlin and Soskice
  - teaching material
  - R

references:
